1. This is true.
2. The httpCodeFilter is configured in the properties so it should never change unless the APEX engine is restarted and the properties are re-read.

To overcome this we could create a field for the compiled pattern in the ApexRestClientConsumer class and compile it in the "init()" method.

private Pattern httpCodeFilterPattern;

..........Blah.......

public void init(.................) {

    ..........................
    httpCodeFilterPattern = Pattern.compile(restConsumerProperties.getHttpCodeFilter());
}

Then the code above becomes:

Matcher isPass = httpCodeFilterPattern().matcher(String.valueOf(response.getStatus()));

if (!isPass.matches()) {

